4%20women's%20NCAA%20championship%20game%20between%20the%20University%20of%20Iowa%20and%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Carolina%20drew%2018.9%20million%20viewers%2C%20according%20to%20the%20media%20audience%20measurement%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nielsen.com%2Fnews-center%2F2024%2Fwomens-college-basketball-championship-draws-record-breaking-18-9-million-viewers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENielsen%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20was%2028%25%20more%20than%20the%2014.8%20million%20viewers%20for%20the%20men's%20matchup%20between%20Purdue%20University%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Connecticut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year-to-year%20ratings%20can%20be%20influenced%20by%20which%20teams%20and%20players%20are%20participating.%20However%2C%20using%20data%20from%20Nielsen%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sportsmediawatch.com%2Fncaa-final-four-ratings-history-most-watched-games-cbs-tbs-nbc%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESports%20Media%20Watch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20can%20see%20that%20the%20shift%20in%20popularity%20has%20been%20building%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20starting%20slowly%20in%20the%20late%202010s%2C%20right%20before%20COVID-19%2C%20and%20picking%20up%20speed%20this%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FCwVEf%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22NCAA%20basketball%20championship%20viewership%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22464%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%20and%202016%2C%20the%20men's%20championship%20game%20averaged%2023%20million%20viewers%2C%20nearly%20eight%20times%20the%20size%20of%20the%20women's%20final%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%203%20million.%20Over%20the%20next%20three%20years%2C%20the%20TV%20audience%20for%20the%20women's%20final%20grew%20by%2023%25%20to%20an%20average%20of%203.7%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20two%20years%20following%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%202020%20NCAA%20basketball%20championships%20due%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20the%20women's%20final%20kept%20up%20momentum%2C%20growing%20by%20an%20average%20of%2027%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%20and%202024%2C%20the%20women's%20game%20reached%20new%20levels%2C%20surpassing%20the%20men's%20championships%20thanks%20to%20the%20surging%20star%20power%20of%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20names%20in%20the%20sport.%20That%20includes%20players%20like%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIowa's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaitlin-clark-valuable-womens-college-basketball-player-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECaitlin%20Clark%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20who%20appeared%20in%20both%20finals%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Louisiana%20State%20University's%20Angel%20Reese%20in%202023.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Carolina%20coach%20Dawn%20Staley%20this%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWomen's%20basketball%20popularity%20goes%20beyond%20championship%20game%20ratings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20seen%20other%20evidence%20of%20women's%20college%20basketball's%20emerging%20dominance%20in%20the%20sports%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20provided%20to%20Business%20Insider%20by%20ticket%20marketplace%20StubHub%2C%20there%20was%20more%20demand%20for%20the%20women's%20three%20Final%20Four%20games%20than%20the%20men's%2C%20with%20sales%20surging%2020%25%20faster%20for%20the%20women's%20games%20than%20the%20men's%20once%20the%20teams%20were%20determined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20sale%20prices%20for%20the%20women's%20tickets%20were%20twice%20the%20cost%20of%20men's%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20Final%20Four%20matchups%2C%20tickets%20to%20the%20women's%20championship%20game%20had%20an%20average%20sale%20price%20of%20%24370%2C%20compared%20to%20%24180%20for%20the%20men's%20final%2C%20according%