ced-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eafford%20more%20of%20what%20life%20has%20to%20offer%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20all%20while%20propping%20up%20a%20cottage%20industry%20of%20companies%20catering%20to%20their%20every%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20tricky%20to%20know%20exactly%20how%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-reelected-americans-are-planning-to-flee-in-droves-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmericans%20have%20relocated%20to%20other%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20details%20of%20when%20or%20why.%20But%20as%20of%202023%2C%20there%20were%20almost%20161%20million%20US%20passports%20in%20circulation%2C%20one%20for%20nearly%20half%20of%20all%20Americans.%20(A%20generation%20ago%2C%20only%2010%25%20of%20Americans%20had%20a%20passport.)%20The%20State%20Department%20estimated%20in%202020%20that%20a%20total%20of%209%20million%20US%20citizens%20lived%20abroad%2C%20up%20from%20an%20estimated%205%20million%20in%202010%20%E2%80%94%20though%20those%20numbers%20include%20dual%20citizens%20born%20and%20raised%20abroad.%20The%20nonprofit%20advocacy%20group%20American%20Citizens%20Abroad%20puts%20the%20figure%20closer%20to%204%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20know%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20yearning%20is%20there.%20In%20a%20recent%20poll%20from%20Monmouth%20University%2C%20one-third%20of%20Americans%20said%20they'd%20like%20to%20settle%20in%20another%20country%2C%20compared%20with%20just%2012%25%20who%20said%20the%20same%20in%20a%201995%20Gallup%20poll.%20In%20InterNation's%202023%20survey%20of%2012%2C000%20expats%20from%20172%20countries%2C%20the%20US%20was%20the%20country%20of%20origin%20for%20the%20largest%20share%20of%20the%20expats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20longing%20to%20move%20abroad%20will%20likely%20be%20unsurprising%20to%20anyone%20who%20has%20recently%20gasped%20over%20their%20weekly%20grocery%20bill%20or%20chipped%20in%20on%20an%20acquaintance's%20medical%20GoFundMe%20with%20a%20six-figure%20goal.%20The%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20reported%20that%20the%20average%20US%20household's%20monthly%20expenses%20jumped%20from%20%245%2C111%20in%202020%20to%20%246%2C081%20in%202022.%20In%20a%20new%20Financial%20Technology%20Association%20survey%2C%2061%25%20of%20American%20workers%20indicated%20they%20were%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20what%3F%20Though%20there's%20no%20question%20that%20Americans%20enjoy%20a%20higher%20material%20standard%20of%20living%20than%20most%20of%20the%20world%2C%20the%20nation%20measures%20poorly%20against%20its%20wealthy%20Western%20peers%20on%20several%20quality-of-life%20indexes%3A%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fwcmsp5%2Fgroups%2Fpublic%2F---ed_protect%2F---protrav%2F---travail%2Fdocuments%2Fpublication%2Fwcms_864222.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F08%2F10%2Fmore-than-4-in-10-u-s-workers-dont-take-all-their-paid-time-off%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evacation%20less%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20spend%20more%20on%20healthcare%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecdbetterlifeindex.org%2Fcountries%2Funited-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edie%20sooner%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20people%20in%20other%20high-income%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20factors%20likely%20explain%20why%20some%20Americans%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-10-places-live-work-abroad-expat-survey-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20to%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20aren't%20generally%20considered%20low-cost-of-living%20locales.%20Data%20from%20the%20global%20recruitment%20firm%20Deel%20suggests%20the%20UK%2C%20Germany%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20France%20are%20among%20the%20top%20seven%20international%20destinations%20for%20American%20job%20seekers.%20In%20places%20with%20universal%20healthcare%2C%20government-subsidized%20childcare%2C%20and%20cultures%20that%20encourage%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance%2C%20your%20dollar%20can%20stretch%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMaliya%20Fale%2C%20a%2022-year-old%20digital%20nomad%20and%20content%20creator%20from%20Minneapolis%2C%20had%20been%20traveling%20through%20Latin%20America%20off%20and%20on%20for%20nearly%20three%20years%20when%2C%20in%20February%2C%20she%20left%20the%20US%20for%20good.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20genuinely%20going%20crazy%20having%20to%20live%20in%20a%20toxic%20American%20capitalist%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40g0v3rnmentnamehere%2Fvideo%2F7314023192245325098%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20TikTok%20video%20titled%20%26quot%3BMoving%20out%20of%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20spoke%20in%20March%2C%20Fale%20was%20staying%20in%20the%20coastal%20town%20of%20Puerto%20Morelos%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20scoping%20out%20her%20next%20move.%20She%20said%20that%20living%20abroad%20afforded%20her%20a%20degree%20of%20flexibility%20and%20spontaneity%20that%20would%20be%20out%20of%20reach%20back%20home.%20She%20supports%20herself%20with%20remote%20content%20gigs%20and%20follows%20whichever%20adventures%20come%20her%20way.%20%26quot%3BThe%20cost%20of%20America%20is%20not%20going%20to%20allow%20me%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20who%20have%20followed%20similar%20paths%20say%20they've%20never%20looked%20back.%20In%20November%202015%2C%20the%20writer%20Cristina%20Johnson%20packed%20three%20suitcases%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-woman-saved-enough-cash-living-abroad-to-build-home-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboarded%20a%20one-way%20flight%20from%20Pennsylvania%20to%20Belize%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Johnson%2C%20now%2053%2C%20has%20a%20disability%20that%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20hold%20down%20enough%20work%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20in%20the%20States.%20In%20Belize%2C%20where%20her%20monthly%20expenses%20are%20a%20mere%20%24250%2C%20Johnson%20has%20been%20able%20to%20build%20a%20home%20and%20save%20thousands%20while%20earning%20about%20%241%2C200%20a%20month%20as%20a%20content-marketing%20copywriter.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20not%20even%20venture%20a%20guess%20on%20how%20much%20I've%20saved%20over%20the%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider%20last%20year%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20even%20if%20I%20saved%20a%20million%20dollars%2C%20it%20would%20not%20be%20as%20valuable%20as%20the%20mental%2C%20emotional%2C%20physical%2C%20and%20psychological%20things%20I%20have%20gained.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20never%20been%20easier%20for%20Americans%20to%20test%20international%20waters%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20in%20countries%20where%20greenbacks%20can%20stretch%20much%20further%20than%20they%20would%20in%20a%20typical%20US%20city.%20More%20than%2050%20countries%20offer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcountries-with-digital-nomad-visas-list-income-requirements-spain-portugal-malta-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigital-nomad%20visas%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20remote%20workers%20able%20to%20prove%20they%20have%20enough%20funds%20to%20support%20themselves.%20Combine%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fbond-yields-1980s-strong-dollar-rally-interest-rates-inflation-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrong%20US%20dollar%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20relative%20ease%20of%20obtaining%20remote%20and%20gig-based%20work%20through%20freelancing%20platforms%20such%20as%20Fiverr%20and%20Upwork%2C%20and%20it's%20no%20wonder%20that%20Americans%20of%20all%20ages%20are%20open%20to%20weighing%20their%20options%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20numerous%20companies%20that%20have%20cropped%20up%20to%20meet%20the%20burgeoning%20demand%20is%20Mexico%20Relocation%20Guide%2C%20based%20in%20Austin.%20Founded%20in%202019%20by%20the%20husband-and-wife%20duo%20of%20Mariana%20and%20Dustin%20Lange%2C%20the%20company%20sells%20relocation%20guidebooks%20geared%20toward%20Americans%20who%20are%20interested%20in%20retiring%20early%20or%20reducing%20their%20cost%20of%20living%20without%20compromising%20on%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20very%20careful%20not%20to%20give%20the%20false%20idea%20that%20people%20are%20going%20to%20live%20like%20kings%20on%20pennies%2C%20because%20that's%20not%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Mariana%20Lange%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20people%20do%20see%20that%20they%20can%20increase%20their%20quality%20of%20life%20for%20the%20same%20amount%2C%20or%20even%20a%20lower%20amount%2C%20of%20money.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20that%20while%20some%20farther-flung%20destinations%20offer%20greater%20bang%20per%20buck%20than%20Mexico%2C%20her%20clientele%20of%20mostly%2040-plus%20Americans%20see%20the%20country's%20relative%20proximity%20to%20their%20family%20and%20friends%20back%20home%20as%20a%20fair%20trade-off.%20Some%20are%20even%20able%20to%20keep%20seeing%20their%20primary-care%20providers%20in%20the%20US%20after%20they%20move.%20Since%20the%20pandemic%20lockdowns%20have%20subsided%2C%20Lange's%20business%20has%20boomed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20owners%20in%20other%20arenas%20have%20similarly%20taken%20note%20of%20the%20expanding%20global%20expat%20population.%20Mark%20Zoril%2C%20the%20North%20Carolina-based%20founder%20of%20the%20financial-planning%20firm%20PlanVision%2C%20began%20working%20with%20expat%20clients%20eight%20or%20nine%20years%20ago%2C%20helping%20them%20manage%20cross-border%20assets%20and%20save%20for%20the%20future%20while%20living%20abroad.%20Today%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20a%20high-profile%20endorsement%20from%20Andrew%20Hallam%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BMillionaire%20Expat%2C%26quot%3B%20these%20clients%20account%20for%20a%20significant%20proportion%20of%20his%20company's%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZoril%20said%20most%20of%20his%20clients%20planned%20to%20remain%20abroad%20indefinitely%2C%20largely%20because%20of%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20returning.%20%26quot%3BThey%20just%20haven't%20accumulated%20a%20lot%20of%20assets%20during%20their%20working%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20for%20them%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20States%20would%20be%20a%20challenge.%26quot%3B%20He%20identified%20Central%20America%2C%20Portugal%2C%20and%20Spain%20as%20particularly%20popular%20destinations%20because%20of%20their%20relatively%20low%20costs%20of%20living%20and%20mild%20climates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20he%20hasn't%20noticed%20a%20change%20in%20the%20demographic%20makeup%20of%20his%20expat%20clientele%20%E2%80%94%20people%20in%20their%2030s%20and%2040s%20who%20don't%20have%20large%20savings%20and%20are%20working%20to%20support%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20Zoril%20said%20that%20in%20recent%20years%20these%20customers%20have%20generally%20become%20savvier%20about%20researching%20and%20weighing%20their%20options%2C%20learning%20online%20about%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20they%20can%20live%20inexpensively%2C%20how%20they%20can%20access%20cash%2C%20and%20how%20they%20can%20invest.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20can%20join%20social%20communities%20with%20other%20people%20that%20are%20also%20living%20this%20way.%20They%20have%20a%20better%20support%20network%20of%20people%20they%20can%20reach%20out%20to%20and%20learn%20from%20before%20they%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EExpat%20life%20does%20come%20with%20its%20share%20of%20potential%20downsides.%20A%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20often%20means%20significantly%20reduced%20earnings%2C%20which%20can%20impede%20someone's%20financial%20ability%20to%20return%20home.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-europe-culture-shock-laundry-dryer-difference-explained-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECultural%20differences%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20language%