dia%3F%20Ex-TCS%20Boss%20Explains%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20has%20raised%20India's%20growth%20forecast%20to%206.8%25%20from%20its%20January%20projection%20of%206.5%25%2C%20citing%20bullish%20domestic%20demand%20and%20a%20rising%20working-age%20population.%20With%20this%2C%20India%20remains%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economy%20of%20the%20world%2C%20ahead%20of%20China's%20projected%20growth%20of%204.6%25%20during%20the%20same%20period.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20growth%20in%20emerging%20and%20developing%20Asian%20countries%20is%20expected%20to%20fall%20from%20an%20estimated%205.6%25%20in%202023%20to%205.2%25%20in%202024%20and%204.9%25%20in%202025%2C%20a%20slight%20upward%20revision%20compared%20with%20the%20January%202024%20WEO%20Update.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%20released%20ahead%20of%20the%20annual%20spring%20meetings%20of%20the%20IMF%20and%20the%20World%20Bank%20projects%20another%20year%20of%20slow%20and%20steady%20growth%20for%20the%20global%20economy%2C%20with%20the%20US%20pushing%20world%20output%20through%20headwinds%20from%20lingering%20high%20inflation%2C%20weak%20demand%20in%20China%20and%20Europe%2C%20and%20spillovers%20from%20the%20two%20regional%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF's%20estimate%20is%20below%20the%207%25%20growth%20projected%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20president%20of%20Tata%20Consultancy%20Services%20(TCS)%20Asia%20Pacific%2C%20Girija%20Pande%20told%20NDTV%20that%20%26quot%3BIndia's%20performance%20is%20quite%20stellar%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bthe%20China%20story%20is%20a%20little%20mixed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20(China)%20have%20a%20huge%20debt%20overhang%20between%20the%20local%20governments%20and%20the%20property%20segment.%20They%20need%20to%20address%20that.%20They%20also%20have%20a%20falling%20birth%20rate%20and%20ageing%20population%20and%20there's%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20restructuring%20going%20on%20in%20China.%20The%20IMF%20has%20conservatively%20put%20China's%20growth%20at%204.6%25%20rather%20than%20the%205%25%20which%20the%20government%20has%20estimated%2C%26quot%3B%20asserts%20Mr%20Pande.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20TCS%20boss%20believes%20China's%20growth%20is%20not%20picking%20up%20due%20to%20these%20drawbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20will%20take%20a%20little%20while.%20There%20is%20a%20level%20of%20deflation%20as%20well...so%20the%20Chinese%20growth%2C%20which%20normally%20drives%20the%20Asian%20growth%2C%20has%20actually%20slowed%20down%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20Asia%20as%20well.%20India%20is%20not%20so%20coupled%20with%20China%2C%20so%20India%20is%20growing%20on%20its%20own%20steam%20at%206.5%25%2C%26quot%3B%20argues%20Mr%20Pande.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20IMF%20has%20said%2C%20it%20may%20revise%20China's%20full-year%20GDP%20growth%20forecast%20upwards%2C%20after%20the%20country%20reported%20stronger-than-expected%205.3%25%20growth%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIMF's%20latest%20report%20also%20warned%20that%20while%20inflation%20trends%20are%20encouraging%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20are%20not%20there%20yet%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20medium-term%20growth%20prospects%20remained%20historically%20weak.%20Worryingly%2C%20the%20IMF%20also%20estimates%20that%20there%20will%20be%20more%20scarring%20for%20low-income%20developing%20countries%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20still%20struggling%20to%20turn%20the%20page%20from%20the%20pandemic%20and%20cost-of-living%20crisis.%20As%20a%20group%2C%20these%20low-income%20developing%20countries%20saw%20their%202024%20growth%20forecast%20cut%20to%204.7%25%20from%20an%20estimate%20of%204.9%25%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20few%20challenges%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20which%20is%20worrying%20them.%20You've%20got%20the%20supply%20chain%20problems%20because%20of%20all%20the%20geopolitics%20going%20on%20-%20the%20oil%20prices%2C%20the%20commodity%20prices.%20Secondly%2C%20the%20interest%20rates%20have%20not%20come%20down%20as%20fast%20as%20expected'%2C%20Girija%20Pande%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20potential%20escalation%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20conflict%20after%20Iran's%20rocket%20and%20drone%20attacks%20on%20Israel%2C%20the%20IMF%20believes%20this%20could%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20effect%26quot%3B%20on%20limiting%20growth%20and%20the%20impact%20would%20raise%20oil%20prices%20and%20inflation%2C%20triggering%20tighter%20monetary%20policy%20from%20central%20banks.%20The%20report%20further%20described%20an%20%26quot%3Badverse%20scenario%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20a%20Middle%20East%20escalation%20would%20lead%20to%20a%2015%25%20increase%20in%20oil%20prices%20and%20higher%20shipping%20costs%20would%20hike%20global%20inflation%20by%20about%200.7%20percentage%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20despite%20the%20world%20economy's%20resilient%20outlook%2C%20the%20IMF%20warns%20that%20economic%20growth%20could%20be%20thrown%20off%20course%20by%20the%20continuing%20adverse%20effects%20of%20higher%20interest%20rates%20and%20geopolitical%20tensions%2C%20including%20the%20wars%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%2C%20that%20have%20threatened%20to%20disrupt%20crucial%20trade%20routes%2C%20raising%20energy%20prices%20among%20other%20ramifications.%20The%20IMF%20has%20also%20stressed%20the%20need%20for%20huge%20global%20investments%20for%20a%20green%20and%20climate-resilient%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713346380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F0rqgd4ho_india-economy-generic-reuters_625x300_22_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbusiness-news%2Fwhy-is-chinas-growth-story-different-from-india-ex-tcs-boss-explains-5461389%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20has%20raised%20India's%20growth%20forecast%20to%206.8%25%20from%20its%20January%20projection%20of%206.5%25%2C%20citing%20bullish%