0could%20enter%2C%20stick%2C%20and%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20was%20an%20anxious%20kid.%20I%20couldn't%20relax%20and%20just%20be%20myself%2C%20feel%20okay%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20quirky%20kid%26quot%3B%20because%20I%20felt%20like%20something%20worse%20than%20that%3A%20an%20alien%2C%20a%20human%20anomaly.%20I%20realized%20early%20on%20that%20there%20were%20many%20things%20I%20was%20%26quot%3Bsupposed%26quot%3B%20to%20do%2C%20but%20none%20of%20them%20came%20naturally%20or%20seemed%20logical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20troubling%20still%20was%20that%20much%20of%20it%20didn't%20feel%20like%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do%3B%20it%20felt%20actively%20wrong.%20When%20a%20teacher%20asked%20me%20a%20question%2C%20whether%20on%20a%20test%20or%20in%20class%2C%20I%20typically%20found%20the%20question%20confusing%20and%20often%20unanswerable.%20The%20%26quot%3Bright%26quot%3B%20answer%20seemed%20like%20just%20one%20of%20many%20possibilities.%20So%2C%20most%20of%20my%20school%20years%20were%20an%20exercise%20in%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%2C%20interpret%2C%20and%20fit%20others'%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20puzzle%20for%20my%20teachers%2C%20a%20misfit%20in%20the%20conventional%20academic%20sense%2C%20and%20a%20total%20outcast%20socially.%20Today%2C%20with%20society's%20much%20greater%20understanding%20of%20ADHD%2C%20part%20of%20my%20eventual%20diagnosis%2C%20there%20are%20evidence-based%20approaches%20for%20building%20self-regulation%20skills%20designed%20for%20kids%20(and%20adults).%20But%20at%20that%20time%20and%20in%20that%20place%2C%20the%20only%20option%20was%20to%20wing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESea%20slugs%20were%20essential%20in%20helping%20me%20retrain%20my%20brain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I%20slowly%20gained%20motivation%20and%20became%20more%20persistent.%20I%20didn't%20know%20it%20at%20the%20time%20but%20my%20evolution%20as%20a%20learner%20mirrored%20the%20two%20fundamental%20concepts%20of%20how%20neurons%20change%20and%20grow%20%E2%80%94%20how%20they%20learn%20%E2%80%94%20that%20the%20neuroscientist%20Eric%20Kandel%20would%20someday%20identify%20as%20the%20basis%20that%20sea%20slugs%20and%20humans%20have%20in%20common%20for%20learning%20and%20memory%3A%20habituation%20and%20sensitization%20in%20response%20to%20repeated%20exposure%20to%20stimuli.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHabituation%20means%20that%20we%20become%20less%20reactive%20to%20stimuli%2C%20as%20you%20might%20to%20traffic%20noise%20outside%20your%20window.%20Sensitization%20means%20that%20our%20reaction%20is%20stronger%2C%20as%20happens%20when%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20a%20sound%20or%20a%20smell%20or%20even%20the%20thought%20of%20something%20becomes%20a%20trigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20my%20own%20experiment%2C%20I%20learned%20to%20make%20use%20of%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20discovered%20some%20basic%20ways%20to%20work%20with%20my%20brain%20to%20habituate%20to%20some%20stimuli%20(ordinary%20things%20that%20distracted%20me)%20and%20sensitize%20(sharpen%20my%20attention)%20to%20others%20to%20be%20able%20to%20reel%20in%20my%20wandering%20mind%20and%20redirect%20the%20synaptic%20messaging%20with%20intention.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20in%20the%20room%20where%20I%20studied%20there%20was%20a%20pinball%20machine%20next%20to%20me%20and%20a%20TV%20behind%20me.%20I%20learned%20to%20ignore%20both%20and%20used%20playing%20the%20pinball%20machine%20as%20a%20reward%20for%20finishing%20my%20homework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%20I%20became%20hyperaware%20of%20how%20to%20intentionally%20hijack%20processes%20in%20my%20brain%20this%20way%20to%20be%20less%20reactive%20or%20more%20sharply%20focused%20as%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%3A%20I%20was%20able%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20seemed%20most%20purposeful%2C%20then%20follow%20through%20and%20maximize%20impact%20as%20opportunities%20opened%20up.%20I%20tinkered%20and%20fine-tuned%20until%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20use%20these%20powerful%20tools%20to%20tap%20into%20the%20heightened%20state%20of%20awareness%20and%20deep%20engagement%20that%20I%20call%20%26quot%3Blit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20'lit'%20focus%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20call%20it%20%26quot%3Blit%26quot%3B%20for%20two%20reasons.%20First%2C%20%26quot%3Blit%26quot%3B%20aptly%20describes%20how%20the%20flash%20of%20inspiration%20feels%E2%80%94as%20if%20a%20bright%20light%20flipped%20on%20in%20the%20dark.%20Or%20a%20spark%20has%20set%20your%20thinking%20ablaze.%20When%20you've%20had%20an%20epiphany%2C%20been%20awestruck%2C%20or%20simply%20been%20super%20excited%2C%20you've%20felt%20that%20spark.%20Second%2C%20%26quot%3Blit%26quot%3B%20is%20how%20these%20moments%20appear%20to%20the%20scientists%20who%20study%20them.%20Inside%20the%20brain%20(and%20in%20the%20gut%20as%20well)%2C%20engaged%20states%20activate%20neurons.%20In%20the%20brain%2C%20this%20triggers%20an%20increase%20in%20cerebral%20blood%20flow%20that%20neuroscientists%20can%20see%20when%20they%20use%20functional%20magnetic%20resonance%20imaging%20(fMRI).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20monitor%2C%20this%20oxygenated%20blood%20lights%20up%20an%20otherwise%20gray%20image%20of%20the%20brain%20with%20yellow-orange%20hot%20spots%20of%20activity.%20Emerging%20science%20shows%20that%20this%20neural%20activation%20is%20associated%20not%20only%20with%20particular%20cognitive%20activity%20or%20emotions%20such%20as%20fear%20and%20anger%20but%20also%20with%20love%2C%20awe%2C%20happiness%2C%20fun%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bpeak%20states%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%26quot%3Blit%26quot%3B%20mode%2C%20we%20engage%20at%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20our%20abilities.%20We%20not%20only%20develop%20the%20mental%20muscles%20to%20stay%20focused%2C%20but%20we%20also%20build%20the%20confidence%20and%20the%20dexterity%20to%20riff%20off%20of%20new%20information%20on%20the%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20more%20likely%20to%20use%20our%20critical%20thinking%20skills%2C%20which%20can%20keep%20us%20from%20blindly%20accepting%20what%20we're%20told%2C%20or%20told%20to%20believe%2C%20especially%20when%20our%20intuition%20says%20otherwise.%20We%20find%20it%20easier%20to%20connect%20with%20people%2C%20are%20more%20alive%20to%20the%20possibilities%20all%20around%20us%2C%20and%20are%20better%20able%20to%20capitalize%20upon%20them.%20In%20a%20stream%20of%20ever-replenishing%20energy%2C%20we're%20constantly%20learning%2C%20growing%2C%20creating%2C%20and%20iterating.%20We're%20building%20our%20capacity%20while%20doing%20our%20best%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20honed%20strategies%20that%20enabled%20me%20to%20activate%20my%20brain%20this%20way%20at%20will%2C%20I%20identified%20a%20dozen%20that%20were%20simple%20to%20use%20and%20never%20failed%20to%20open%20my%20thinking%20in%20just%20the%20way%20that%20was%20needed%2C%20whatever%20that%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20was%20to%20direct%20my%20attention%20or%20disrupt%20it%2C%20sharpen%20my%20focus%20or%20broaden%20it%2C%20do%20something%20stimulating%20or%20quiet%20my%20mind%2C%20these%20Life%20Ignition%20Tools%20(LIT)%20worked%20for%20me%2C%20and%20then%20for%20others%20as%20I%20shared%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPracticing%20habits%20that%20let%20me%20access%20deep%20work%20has%20been%20integral%20to%20my%20success%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20work%20with%20my%20neuroatypical%2C%20voraciously%20curious%2C%20but%20chaotic%20brain%2C%20I%20discovered%20infinite%20opportunity%20to%20question%2C%20create%2C%20and%20innovate%20as%20a%20bioengineer%20and%20entrepreneur%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20and%20help%20others%20do%20the%20same.%20These%20LIT%20tools%20took%20me%20from%20being%20a%20confused%20and%20frustrated%20kid%2C%20sidelined%20in%20a%20special%20ed%20classroom%20in%20rural%20Canada%2C%20to%20becoming%20a%20bioengineer%20and%20medical%20innovator%20elected%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20National%20Academy%20of%20Inventors%2C%20the%20Royal%20Society%20of%20Chemistry%2C%20the%20American%20Institute%20for%20Medical%20and%20Biological%20Engineering's%20College%20of%20Fellows%2C%20the%20Biomedical%20Engineering%20Society%2C%20and%20the%20Canadian%20Academy%20of%20Engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20professor%2C%20I've%20trained%20more%20than%20200%20people%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20now%20professors%20at%20institutions%20around%20the%20world%20and%20innovators%20in%20industry%3B%20published%20130%20peer-reviewed%20papers%20with%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20citations%3B%20and%20obtained%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20issued%20or%20pending%20national%20and%20international%20patents.%20The%20tools%20also%20helped%20me%20cofound%2012%20companies%20with%20products%20on%20the%20market%20or%20in%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20finally%2C%20they've%20been%20instrumental%20in%20creating%20a%20productive%2C%20supportive%2C%20and%20dynamic%20high-energy%20environment%20in%20my%20lab%2C%20which%20recently%20morphed%20from%20Karp%20Lab%20to%20the%20Center%20for%20Accelerated%20Medical%20Innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHaving%20specific%20tools%20helped%20a%20struggling%20kid%20like%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELIT%20worked%20for%20this%20kid%20who%20appeared%20to%20show%20no%20promise%20and%20the%20young%20man%20who%20remained%20frustrated%20and%20discouraged%20for%20many%20years.%20Though%20I%20still%20struggle%20every%20day%20in%20various%20ways%2C%20I'm%20grateful%20to%20be%20able%20to%20say%20that%20these%20LIT%20tools%20enabled%20me%20to%20meet%20and%20far%20exceed%20those%20dismal%20early%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20want%20breakthroughs%20in%20science%20and%20medicine%2C%20if%20we%20want%20successful%2C%20disruptive%20innovations%20on%20all%20fronts%20to%20support%20healthier%20communities%2C%20and%20if%20we%20want%20to%20cut%20through%20the%20noise%20and%20focus%20on%20what%20is%20most%20important%2C%20we%20must%20learn%20how%20to%20use%20all%20of%20the%20tools%20in%20nature's%20playbook%2C%20our%20evolutionary%20arsenal.%20We%20must%20shake%20up%20our%20thinking%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20now%20and%20then%20but%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20LIT%20tools%20make%20it%20possible%20for%20us%20to%20take%20anything%20we're%20hardwired%20for%20%E2%80%94%20including%20undesirable%20or%20unhelpful%20behaviors%20and%20habits%20%E2%80%94%20and%20with%20intention%2C%20channel%20the%20energy%20in%20them%20to%20create%20a%20positive%20outcome.%20It's%20easier%20than%20you%20might%20think%20because%20the%20more%20you%20do%20it%2C%20the%20greater%20the%20rewards%2C%20the%20momentum%2C%20and%20your%20impact%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20never%20too%20old%20to%20charge%20your%20brain%20this%20way%2C%20and%20most%20definitely%20no%20one%20is%20ever%20too%20young.%20In%20fact%2C%20LIT%20tools%20can%20be%20lifesavers%20for%20kids%2C%20as%20they%20were%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAdapted%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.harpercollins.com%2Fproducts%2Flit-life-ignition-tools-jeff-karp%3Fvariant%3D41287961280546%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELIT%3A%20Use%20Nature's%20Playbook%20to%20Energize%20Your%20Brain%2C%20Spark%20Ideas%2C%20and%20Ignite%20Action%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20by%20Jeff%20Karp%2C%20PhD%2C%20published%20by%20William%20Morrow.%20Copyright%20%C2%A9%202024%20by%20Jeffrey%20Michael%20Karp.%20Reprinted%20courtesy%20of%20HarperCollinsPublishers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-professor-with-adhd-deep-work-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713345039000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661e47e110c6b0cde5efbe8c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-professor-with-adhd-deep-work-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr.%20Jeff%20Karp%20grew%20up%20with%20undiagnosed%20ADHD%20and%20shares%20how%20he%20overcame%20low%20expectations%20and%20retrained%20his%20brain%20to%20become%20a%20Harvard%20professor.%22%2C%22a