%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20McKinsey%20as%20an%20associate%20in%202021.%20Going%20in%2C%20I%20always%20knew%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20here%20for%20a%20bad%20time%2C%20not%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-burnout-quit-elitist-consulting-lifestyle-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20would%20be%20challenging%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20also%20hoped%20that%20if%20I%20stuck%20it%20out%2C%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20build%20up%20my%20analytical%20toolkit%20and%20learn%20how%20to%20problem-solve%20really%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20looking%20back%2C%20I%20regret%20the%20way%20I%20approached%20my%20time%20at%20McKinsey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20was%20little%20apprenticeship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20I%20struggled%20with%20was%20the%20lack%20of%20apprenticeship.%20It's%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Ffeatured-insights%2Fpeople-in-progress%2Fembracing-apprenticeship-as-a-way-of-life-a-new-definition-for-an-old-idea%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapprenticeship-heavy%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20my%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20expected%20to%20start%20working%20from%20day%20one.%20I%20was%20there%20to%20learn%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20frustrating%20experience%20because%20no%20one%20was%20there%20to%20teach%20me.%20I%20wanted%20somebody%20to%20sit%20down%20with%20me%20and%20teach%20me%20the%20basic%20skills%20required%20for%20the%20job%2C%20like%20how%20to%20problem-solve%20for%20a%20meeting%2C%20how%20to%20wordsmith%20a%20deck%2C%20and%20how%20to%20fix%20my%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20alone%20on%20an%20island%20while%20my%20manager%20drowned%20in%20her%20other%20work.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20wasn't%20learning%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20I%20heard%20senior-level%20employees%20commenting%20about%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-firm-new-hires-consultants-mba-get-paid-do-nothing-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20analysts%20and%20associates%20weren't%20good%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20weren't%20receiving%20any%20apprenticeship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20typically%20worked%20from%207%3A30%20a.m.%20until%2011%3A30%20p.m.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20consultants%2C%20we%20didn't%20have%20to%20do%20any%20hardcore%20research%20because%20we%20had%20teams%20that%20did%20our%20research%20for%20us.%20We%20also%20had%20a%20team%20we%20could%20call%20on%20if%20we%20needed%20help%20with%20Excel%2C%20a%20team%20to%20make%20our%20PowerPoints%20pretty%2C%20and%20a%20team%20to%20set%20up%20calls%20with%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20funny%20because%20people%20ask%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20had%20all%20those%20researchers%2C%20so%20what%20did%20%3Cem%3Eyou%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20days%20mainly%20consisted%20of%20problem-solving%20meetings%20in%20which%20we'd%20show%20the%20partners%20or%20senior%20partners%20our%20decks%20and%20get%20their%20feedback%2C%20take%20notes%2C%20and%20then%20revise%20accordingly%20before%20the%20next%20meeting%2C%20which%20might%20be%20later%20that%20same%20day%20or%20the%20following%20day.%20Sometimes%20I'd%20have%20three%20of%20these%20meetings%20a%20day%2C%20all%20on%20different%20decks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20had%20to%20spend%20time%20doing%20analyses%20for%20new%20pages%20in%20the%20deck%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20client%20meetings%20and%20on%20calls%20with%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20typical%20day%2C%20I%20worked%20from%207%3A30%20a.m.%20or%208%20a.m.%20until%2011%3A30%20p.m.%20And%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburnout-consulting-firms-deloitte-pwc-big-four-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epedal%20to%20the%20metal%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20leave%20my%20desk%2C%20forgot%20to%20eat%2C%20and%20dropped%20tons%20of%20weight.%20I%20barely%20remembered%20to%20go%20to%20the%20bathroom.%20I%20only%20remembered%20to%20get%20up%20when%20I%20noticed%20my%20dog%20looking%20at%20me%20all%20sad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20although%20we%20had%20a%20budget%20for%20fun%20work%20events%2C%20some%20people%20didn't%20like%20attending%20them%20because%20they'd%20still%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20work%20waiting%20for%20them%20when%20they%20got%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20had%20many%20team%20dinners%20where%20some%20people%20would%20call%20their%20Uber%20secretly%20underneath%20the%20table%20so%20they%20could%20get%20home%20and%20keep%20working.%20It%20kind%20of%20took%20the%20fun%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bar%20at%20McKinsey%20was%20much%20higher%20than%20at%20my%20previous%20consulting%20firm%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20like%20people%20love%20to%20hate%20consultants.%20They%20say%20that%20consultants%20just%20take%20companies'%20money%20and%20don't%20add%20value.%20But%20many%20consulting%20firms%20get%20projects%20based%20on%20results%20and%20outcomes%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-management-consulting-firms-in-the-us-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcKinsey%20couldn't%20be%20McKinsey%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20read%20comments%20on%20social%20media%20that%20assume%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-of-consultants-top-firms-pwc-deloitte-ey-bain-mckinsey-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverpaid%20idiots%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20McKinsey.%20But%20there%20really%20aren't%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20an%20attitude%20of%20%26quot%3Bmove%20up%20or%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20people%20there%20are%20really%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20the%20chance%20to%20solve%20a%20lot%20of%20ambiguous%20problems%20with%20some%20really%20good%20problem-solvers.%20The%20company%20really%20goes%20out%20of%20its%20way%20to%20give%20clients%20a%20bespoke%20experience%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-of-consultants-accountants-big-4-deloitte-kpmg-ey-pwc-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Four%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20which%20is%20more%20of%20a%20plug-and-chug%20into%20the%20same%20slide%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20previously%20worked%20at%20another%20consulting%20firm%2C%20and%20my%20experience%20there%20compared%20to%20McKinsey%20was%20like%20night%20and%20day.%20The%20work%20at%20McKinsey%20was%20so%20much%20harder%2C%20and%20the%20bar%20was%20so%20much%20higher.%20Everything%20at%20McKinsey%20is%20just%20a%20lot%20more%20customized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20associate%20partners%20and%20partners%20were%20mean%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20at%20McKinsey%20were%20both%20the%20best%20and%20worst%20parts%20of%20my%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20and%20associates%20were%20all%20cool%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-cope-with-a-bad-boss-at-work-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20few%20associate%20partners%20and%20partners%20were%20mean%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20freaked%20out%20over%20mistakes%20and%20belittled%20people's%20thought%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20McKinsey%20friends%20always%20said%20I%20got%20really%20unlucky%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20associate%20partners%20I%20had%20to%20work%20closely%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20wasn't%20an%20everyday%20thing%2C%20they%20made%20some%20analysts%20and%20associates%20cry.%20One%20associate%20partner%20looked%20at%20a%20slide%20I%20made%2C%20began%20laughing%20hysterically%2C%20and%20said%20it%20was%20the%20worst%20slide%20they%20had%20ever%20seen.%20Another%20associate%20partner%20yelled%20at%20and%20made%20fun%20of%20people%20while%20talking%20about%20them%20behind%20their%20backs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20also%20to%20their%20faces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20of%20my%20favorite%20memories%20also%20involves%20the%20people%20at%20McKinsey.%20One%20time%2C%20an%20associate%20partner%20screamed%20at%20me%20in%20front%20of%20our%20whole%20team%20because%20they%20wrongfully%20thought%20I%20was%20going%20to%20miss%20a%20deadline%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20knew%20I%20could%20meet%20it%20and%20didn't%20end%20up%20missing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20crying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20team%20felt%20so%20bad%20for%20me%20that%20they%20rallied%20behind%20me%20and%20we%20all%20stopped%20working%20for%20the%20night.%20One%20of%20my%20coworkers%20went%20and%20got%20bottles%20of%20wine%2C%20and%20we%20all%20drank%20in%20the%20team%20room%3B%20it%20just%20felt%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20camaraderie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20took%20a%20mental%20health%20break%20because%20I%20couldn't%20do%20it%20anymore%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20a%20year%20of%20working%20at%20McKinsey%2C%20I%20took%20a%20three-month%20mental%20health%20leave.%20It%20was%20literally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fall-the-signs-that-your-job-is-wreaking-havoc-on-your-mental-health-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edriving%20me%20to%20the%20edge%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20just%20couldn't%20do%20it%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20crying%20more%20and%20taking%20anxiety%20medication%20at%20a%20higher%20dosage%20than%20I%20had%20ever%20needed%20before%20joining.%20The%20week%20before%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%2C%20I%20was%20oscillating%20between%20being%20way%20too%20OK%2C%20and%20then%20crying%2C%20and%20then%20being%20way%20too%20stoic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-talk-to-your-boss-about-your-mental-health-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%20with%20my%20development%20group%20leader%20(DGL)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20mentor%20assigned%20by%20McKinsey%2C%20that%20I%20was%20thinking%20about%20taking%20short-term%20mental%20health%20disability%20leave.%20I%20wasn't%20even%20nervous%20about%20bringing%20this%20up%20because%20of%20how%20normal%20it%20seemed%20%E2%80%94%20I%20know%20other%20McKinsey%20employees%20who%20have%20also%20taken%20health%20breaks%20due%20to%20the%20mental%20toll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20McKinsey%2C%20I%20didn't%20even%20know%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fdisability%2Fprofessionals%2Fbluebook%2F12.00-MentalDisorders-Adult.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20health%20disability%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20a%20thing.%20Now%20I%20know%20more%20than%20a%20few%20people%20who%20have%20gotten%20them.%20The%20mental%20toll%2C%20plus%20the%20workload%2C%20was%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20heard%20multiple%20people%2C%20myself%20included%2C%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20get%20paid%20enough%20for%20this%20shit%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20genuinely%20believe%20that.%20I%20don't%20think%20that%20the%20pay%20was%20enough%20for%20what%20we%20were%20doing%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20was%20making%20over%20%24200%2C000%20when%20I%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20break%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20pick%20up%20new%20hobbies%20and%20realized%20that%20I%20hated%20every%20hobby.%20I%20tried%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20house%20more%20but%20wasn't%20really%20successful%20because%20of%20how%20down%20I%20was.%20Sometimes%2C%20I'd%20have%20to%20hire%20a%20dog%20walker%20even%20though%20I%20was%20home%20because%20I%20just%20felt%20like%20I%20couldn't%20handle%20it.%20At%20some%20point%2C%20I%20couldn't%20even%20care%20for%20myself%2C%20so%20my%20mom%20came%20to%20town%20to%20care%20for%20me%20and%20my%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20officially%20leave%20because%20I%20realized%20if%20working%20here%20caused%20my%20mental%20health%20to%20deteriorate%2C%20why%20would%20I%20stay%3F%20Why%20would%20I%20want%20to%20be%20someplace%20that%20causes%20me%20to%20be%20in%20such%