0all%20thanks%20to%20the%20blockade%20that%20made%20life%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20such%20a%20struggle%20for%20the%20past%2016%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20satellite%20images%2C%20the%20UN%20cultural%20organisation%20reckons%20some%2041%20historic%20sites%20have%20been%20damaged%20since%20Israel%20began%20pounding%20the%20besieged%20territory%20after%20the%20October%207%20Hamas%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20ground%2C%20Palestinian%20archaeologist%20Fadel%20al-Otol%20keeps%20tabs%20on%20the%20destruction%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20has%20electricity%20and%20internet%20access%2C%20photos%20pour%20into%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20he%20set%20up%20with%2040%20or%20so%20young%20peers%20he%20mobilised%20to%20watch%20over%20the%20territory's%20vast%20array%20of%20ancient%20sites%20and%20monuments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20teenager%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20Otol%20was%20hired%20by%20European%20archaeological%20missions%20before%20going%20on%20to%20study%20in%20Switzerland%20and%20at%20the%20Louvre%20Museum%20in%20Paris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20archaeological%20remains%20in%20the%20north%20have%20been%20hit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP%20by%20phone%20from%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20human%20toll%20since%20the%20October%207%20Hamas%20attack%20has%20been%20chilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%201%2C170%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20unprecedented%20raid%20on%20Israel%2C%20according%20to%20an%20AFP%20tally%20of%20Israeli%20official%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%2034%2C000%20have%20died%20in%20Gaza%20in%20unrelenting%20Israeli%20retaliation%2C%20according%20to%20the%20territory's%20health%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20damage%20to%20Gaza's%20history%20has%20also%20been%20immense.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENapoleon's%20HQ%20flattened%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBlakhiya%20(the%20ancient%20Greek%20city%20of%20Anthedon)%20was%20directly%20bombed.%20There's%20a%20huge%20hole%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20Otol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20part%20of%20the%20site%2C%20near%20a%20Hamas%20barracks%20where%20%26quot%3Bwe%20hadn't%20started%20excavating%26quot%3B%2C%20was%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2013th-century%20Al-Basha%20palace%20in%20Gaza%20City's%20old%20town%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20completely%20destroyed.%20There%20was%20bombing%20and%20(then)%20it%20was%20bulldozed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20held%20hundreds%20of%20ancient%20objects%20and%20magnificent%20sarcophagi%2C%26quot%3B%20Otol%20added%20as%20he%20shared%20recent%20photos%20of%20the%20ruins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENapoleon%20is%20said%20to%20have%20based%20himself%20in%20the%20ochre%20stone%20edifice%20at%20the%20disastrous%20end%20of%20his%20Egyptian%20campaign%20in%201799.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20room%20where%20the%20French%20emperor%20supposedly%20slept%20was%20full%20of%20Byzantine%20artefacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20best%20finds%20were%20displayed%20in%20the%20Basha%2C%26quot%3B%20Jean-Baptiste%20Humbert%20of%20the%20French%20Biblical%20and%20Archaeological%20School%20in%20Jerusalem%20(EBAF)%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20know%20little%20of%20their%20fate%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BDid%20someone%20remove%20the%20objects%20before%20blowing%20the%20building%20up%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENerves%20were%20frayed%20even%20further%20when%20the%20director%20of%20Israeli%20Antiquities%2C%20Eli%20Escusido%2C%20posted%20a%20video%20on%20Instagram%20of%20Israeli%20soldiers%20surrounded%20by%20vases%20and%20ancient%20pottery%20in%20the%20EBAF%20warehouse%20in%20Gaza%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20what%20has%20been%20unearthed%20in%20digs%20in%20Gaza%20was%20stored%20either%20at%20the%20Al-Basha%20museum%20or%20the%20warehouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestinians%20quickly%20accused%20the%20army%20of%20pillaging.%20But%20EBAF%20archaeologist%20Rene%20Elter%20said%20he%20has%20seen%20no%20evidence%20of%20%26quot%3Bstate%20looting%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20colleagues%20were%20able%20to%20return%20to%20the%20site.%20The%20soldiers%20opened%20boxes.%20We%20don't%20know%20if%20they%20took%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20when%20Fadel%20(al-Otol)%20calls%20me%2C%20I'm%20afraid%20he'll%20tell%20me%20that%20one%20of%20our%20colleagues%20has%20died%20or%20that%20such%20and%20such%20a%20site%20has%20been%20destroyed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArchaeology%20is%20a%20highly%20political%20issue%20in%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20territories%2C%20with%20discoveries%20often%20used%20to%20justify%20the%20claims%20of%20the%20two%20warring%20peoples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Israel%20has%20an%20army%20of%20archaeologists%20who%20have%20unearthed%20an%20impressive%20number%20of%20ancient%20treasures%2C%20Gaza%20remains%20relatively%20untouched%20by%20the%20trowel%20despite%20a%20rich%20past%20stretching%20back%20thousands%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAncient%20crossroads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20sheltered%20natural%20harbour%20between%20the%20Sinai%20and%20Lebanon%2C%20Gaza%20has%20been%20for%20centuries%20a%20crossroads%20of%20civilisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20pivot%20point%20between%20Africa%20and%20Asia%20and%20a%20hub%20of%20the%20incense%20trade%2C%20it%20was%20coveted%20by%20the%20Egyptians%2C%20Persians%2C%20Greeks%2C%20Romans%20and%20Ottomans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20figure%20in%20excavating%20this%20glorious%20past%20over%20the%20last%20few%20decades%20has%20been%20Jawdat%20Khoudary%2C%20a%20Gazan%20construction%20magnate%20and%20collector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGaza%2C%20with%20its%20%26quot%3Bseafront%20real%20estate%26quot%3B%2C%20had%20a%20property%20boom%20in%20the%201990s%20after%20the%20Oslo%20peace%20accords%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20building%20workers%20dug%20up%20the%20soil%2C%20they%20came%20across%20lots%20and%20lots%20of%20ancient%20objects.%20Khoudary%20amassed%20a%20treasure%20trove%20of%20artefacts%20that%20he%20opened%20up%20to%20foreign%20archaeologists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarc-Andre%20Haldimann%2C%20then%20curator%20of%20MAH%2C%20Geneva's%20art%20and%20history%20museum%2C%20couldn't%20believe%20his%20eyes%20when%20he%20was%20invited%20to%20have%20a%20look%20around%20the%20garden%20of%20Khoudary's%20mansion%20in%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20ourselves%20in%20front%20of%204%2C000%20objects%2C%20including%20an%20avenue%20of%20Byzantine%20columns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuickly%20an%20idea%20took%20shape%20to%20organise%20a%20major%20exhibition%20to%20highlight%20Gaza's%20past%20at%20the%20MAH%2C%20and%20then%20to%20build%20a%20museum%20in%20the%20territory%20itself%20so%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20could%20take%20ownership%20of%20their%20own%20heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%202006%2C%20around%20260%20objects%20from%20the%20Khoudary%20collection%20left%20Gaza%20for%20Geneva%2C%20with%20some%20later%20going%20on%20to%20be%20part%20of%20another%20hit%20show%20at%20the%20Institut%20du%20Monde%20Arabe%20(IMA)%20in%20Paris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20geopolitics%20changed%20along%20the%20way.%20In%20June%202007%2C%20Hamas%20drove%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20from%20Gaza.%20And%20Israel%20imposed%20its%20blockade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Gazan%20artefacts%20could%20no%20longer%20return%20home%20and%20remained%20stuck%20in%20Geneva%2C%20while%20the%20archaeological%20museum%20project%20fizzled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Khoudary%20did%20not%20give%20up%20hope.%20He%20built%20a%20museum-hotel%20called%20Al-Mathaf%2C%20museum%20in%20Arabic%2C%20on%20the%20Mediterranean%20coast%20north%20of%20Gaza%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20came%20the%20Israeli%20ground%20offensive%20after%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20October%207%2C%20which%20began%20in%20Gaza's%20north.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Anything%20but%20a%20black%20hole'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAl-Mathaf%20remained%20under%20Israeli%20control%20for%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20Khoudary%2C%20who%20fled%20Gaza%20for%20Egypt%2C%20told%20AFP.%20%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20they%20left%2C%20I%20asked%20some%20people%20to%20go%20there%20to%20see%20what%20state%20the%20place%20was%20in.%20I%20was%20shocked.%20Several%20items%20were%20missing%20and%20the%20hall%20had%20been%20set%20on%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20mansion%20was%20also%20destroyed%20during%20fierce%20fighting%20in%20the%20Sheikh%20Radwan%20neighbourhood%20of%20Gaza%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Israelis%20flattened%20the%20garden%20with%20bulldozers...%20I%20don't%20know%20whether%20objects%20were%20buried%20(by%20the%20bulldozers)%20or%20whether%20the%20marble%20columns%20were%20broken%20or%20looted.%20I%20can't%20find%20words%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20military%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20specific%20sites.%20But%20it%20accused%20Hamas%20of%20systematically%20using%20civilian%20structures%20like%20cultural%20heritage%20sites%2C%20government%20buildings%2C%20schools%2C%20shelters%20and%20hospitals%20for%20military%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsrael%20maintains%20its%20commitments%20to%20international%20law%2C%20including%20by%20affording%20the%20necessary%20special%20protections%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20army%20added%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20part%20of%20Khoudary's%20collection%20has%20been%20lost%2C%20the%20treasures%20held%20in%20Switzerland%20remain%20intact%2C%20saved%20by%20the%20blockade%20and%20the%20red%20tape%20that%20delayed%20their%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20106%20crates%20ready%20to%20go%26quot%3B%20for%20years%2C%20said%20Beatrice%20Blandin%2C%20the%20MAH%20museum's%20current%20curator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESafely%20far%20from%20the%20war%20raging%20in%20Gaza%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20objects%20are%20in%20good%20condition%26quot%3B%2C%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20restored%20some%20of%20the%20bronze%20pieces%20that%20were%20slightly%20corroded%20and%20repacked%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20had%20to%20be%20sure%20that%20the%20convoy%20would%20not%20be%20blocked%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20AFP.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20waiting%20for%20that%20green%20light.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20any%20return%20impossible%20for%20the%20moment%2C%20Blandin%20said%20%26quot%3Bdiscussions%20are%20under%20way%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20new%20Gaza%20exhibition%20in%20Switzerland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhoudary%20is%20excited%20by%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20collection%20of%20objects%20on%20the%20history%20of%20Gaza%20is%20in%20Geneva.%20If%20there%20is%20a%20new%20show%2C%20it%20will%20allow%20the%20whole%20world%20to%20learn%20about%20our%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP%20from%20Cairo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20irony%20of%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Haldimann%2C%20who%20is%20trying%20to%20get%20his%20friend%20Fadel%20al-Otol%20safely%20out%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20new%20Gaza%20exhibition%20would%20show%20once%20again%20that%20Gaza...%20is%20anything%20but%20a%20black%20hole.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713334020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fhehkikq_gaza-palace-napoleon-bonaparte-_625x300_17_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgazas-historic-treasures-saved-by-irony-of-history-5460148%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gaza's%20ancient%20Greek%20site%20of%20Anthedon%20has%20been%20bombed%2C%20its%20%26quot%3BNapoleon's%20Palace%26quot%3B%20destro